  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving access to sanitation and water for urban slum dwellers</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to improve access to water and sanitation services for 3,000 people living in the urban settlements of Mukuru and Korogocho in Nairobi. This will be achieved by: (1) building two environmentally friendly bio -sanitation centres to provide dignified and clean hygiene facilities for 1,000 users, (2) create two water points to allow 3,000 people to gain access to reasonably priced water by linking the settlement to the city water systems, and (3) provide training for 200 community members in construction, maintenance and bio -centre management to enable them to run the centres.</narrative>
  </description>
